    'description' => 'Monitor a directory for file changes across tool calls. Scans a directory tree, computes checksums (MD5/SHA256) for all files, persists the manifest to a SQLite database, and on subsequent runs reports what changed: new files, modified files, deleted files, and unchanged files. Uses file hashing for content comparison (not just timestamps) to detect true modifications. First unattended integrity monitoring capability in the ecosystem. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
